 Soni Daniel – Abuja Despite exposing the suspects in the botched Process and Industrial Development gas processing and supply contract, the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Chairman,  Ibrahim Magu, may not withstand the renewed plots by his traducers to get him out of his exalted position. The renewed attempts to remove him, according to competent sources, stem from steps he has taken to expose the shenanigans involved in the botched controversial contract, which resulted in a princely $9.6 billion fine against Nigeria. Continue reading P&ID’s $9.6bn scam: Magu may be axed at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard